Author: Raynx
Text: I can immensely relate to this. I actually didn't even want to start applying to other jobs before achieving my GW, out of some misguided sentiment that I wasn't good enough as myself for them, so I should be thinner to "compensate" for it.  Well, spoiler : not only did I never achieve my GW, but companies really don't give a shit about the excess 10 pounds on the person in front of them. In the end, I got my new job 10 months ago; those 10 months would've been lost if I were still waiting.  It's a numbers game. Hang in there and keep going!
